    <div class="step-title">
      1. To install RVM, type this in your Terminal
    </div>
    <div class="step-code">
      <span style="color:rgb(40,160,160)">$</span> \curl -L https://get.rvm.io | bash -s stable
    </div>
    <div class="step-title">
      2. Close your Terminal and re-open it. Then type
    </div>
    <div class="step-code">
      <span style="color:rgb(40,160,160)">$</span> source ~/.rvm/scripts/rvm<br>
      <span style="color:rgb(40,160,160)">$</span> touch .bash_profile <br>
      <span style="color:rgb(40,160,160)">$</span> open .bash_profile
    </div>
    <div class="step-title">
      3. Paste this into your new .bash_profile then save and close
    </div>
    <div class="step-code">
      <span style="color:rgb(40,160,160)">$</span> PATH=$PATH:$HOME/.rvm/bin # Add RVM to PATH for scripting  [[ -s "$HOME/.rvm/scripts/rvm" ]] && . "$HOME/.rvm/scripts/rvm" # Load RVM function
    </div>
    <div class="step-title">
      3. Now install Ruby by typing in 
    </div>
    <div class="step-code">
      <span style="color:rgb(40,160,160)">$</span> rvm install 2.1.0<br>
      <span style="color:rgb(40,160,160)">$</span> rvm use 2.1.0 -default<br>
      <span style="color:rgb(40,160,160)">$</span> ruby -v
    </div>
    <div class="step-tip">
      <strong>PRO TIP</strong>: <span style="color:yellow">Installing Ruby</span> takes a while, go grab a cup of coffee
    </div>
    <div class="step-title">
      4. Additions actions thay may be needed
    </div>
    <div class="step-tip">
      <strong>1.</strong> If you get an entire page of instructions, beginning with “Ruby (and needed base gems) for your selection…”, you should <span style="color:yellow">press Q to skip</span><br><br>
      <strong>2.</strong> If RVM reports an error, run <br>
      <span style="color:yellow">$</span> rvm requirements<br><br>
      <strong>3.</strong> Any "Missing Required Package" statements can be resolved by entering<br>
      <span style="color:yellow">$</span> brew install *missing package name* <br><br>
      Example: <span style="color:yellow">$</span> brew install autoconf automake libtool pkg-config apple-gcc42 libyaml readline libxml2 libxslt libksba openssl sqlite imagemagick

